\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3149352 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1079458\charrsid11799661 Yes we'd get another }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid91116\charrsid11799661 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1079458\charrsid11799661  another year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1199167 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1079458\charrsid11799661 So you always had a couple of pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3149352 RJ  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1079458\charrsid11799661 Not always - after we'd killed saying as probably now we should stop till about March or April till we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid91116\charrsid11799661 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1079458\charrsid11799661  more. That's how we used to work it in. If we had them about March or April we used to keep them till about Christmas time and then kill them.
